import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['rate'] = data['rate'].astype(float)
    avg_rate = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = avg_rate.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the average obesity rate across all states?')
    ax.legend([f'Average Rate: {avg_rate.mean():.2f}'])
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.hist(data['rate'], bins=20)
    ax.set_xlabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values('rate', ascending=False)
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.bar(data['state'], data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which state has the highest obesity rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['rate'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max rate: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of obesity rate over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
